HEADWORD: mail bag
<hw>mail bag</hw></mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A
bag in which mailed matter is conveyed or shipped under public
authority.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> mail pouch.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A letter carrier's shoulder bag; <as>as, in England
they call a <ex>mailbag</ex> a postbag</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> postbag.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

